         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... she says: Oh lord, do not speak thus! One ... thing is just not seen in dreams. There is no thing ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Ein ... Ding wird eben in Träumen nicht gesehen.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">A ... thing is just not seen in dreams.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>232</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4 #a5 #a6 #b1 #b2 #b3 #b4 #b5 #b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:sieg1952"/><citedRange>10-11</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>132</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>95</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (If) they should be, still (on earth) they will be seen [only] once; together, however, these things are [to be found] all in the ocean. (If) ... come (?) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>289</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2012a"/><citedRange>203</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the vision, oh great king. [He who] has educated himself in this matter in an earlier time, [he] (will ...) such a unique vision ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1972"/><citedRange>450</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1972"/><citedRange>457</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the third vision, too, of which there will certainly be fear. [To?] him, who has seen the fourth vision, belongs ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">… the third image, for which there will certainly be fear.  (cf 10)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>629</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>305</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... remembers. You know my dream, with it ... you have been called by me ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (When he had heard this, the king) like a ruler with all friendliness says to the queen: Thus shall it be, oh noble one. I will send out (hunters) ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">So it will be, o noble one. I will send (hunters).  (cf 11)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>624</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>293</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1981"/><citedRange>490</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>52</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... After (the king) had gathered (the hunters), he says: Go then, skilled ones! The elephant, who has been seen by the queen in a dream, (does he exist or does he not (?)) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... When they had heard this, the old hunters say (to the king): Oh lord, these (locks (?)) of our hair ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>302</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... ([but] never) we had heard: There is such an elephant. And how should we have seen [it]? ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">How should we have seen [it]?  (cf 11)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>631</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>27</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>24</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (If) you bring the tusks of the (ele)phant, [it is] well. If (, however,) you do not bring [them], I will arrange for the (killing) [of you] all to the seventh lineage ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(If) you bring me the tusks of the elephant, [it is] good. (But) if you do not bring [them], I will cause [your] (death) [and that of your] relatives up to the seventh [degree].  (cf 11)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>638</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (wenn) ihr die Stoßzähne des Elefanten bringt, [ist es] gut. Wenn ihr [sie] (aber) nicht bringt, werde ich bis zum siebenten Geschlecht insgesamt [eure] (Tötung) veranlassen.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... (if) you bring the elephant's tusks, [it is] well. (But) if you do not bring [them], I will arrange for [your] (killing) entirely until the seventh generation.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>391</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... The queen thought: Never will there be (a hunter) who (finds (?)) the elephant without instruction ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... After the queen thereupon had called the old hunters (together, she speaks to the one), who among them (was versed (?) in) the fivefold art of archery ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
